<p>This program is responsible for ensuring that human and animal drugs; biologicals; and cosmetics are safe, properly labeled, do not contain harmful additives and do not make any unsubstantiated or fraudulent claims.</p> 
<p>Businesses engaged in the distribution or manufacture of an over-the-counter (OTC) drug or a prescription drug are required to license with the Texas Department of State Health Services (DSHS).</p>

<h2>Licensing</h2>
<p>The Drugs and Medical Devices Group conducts inspections of manufacturers, distributors and retailers of drugs and cosmetic products to assess and enforce compliance with applicable state and federal requirements. For more information on becoming licensed, please see the <a title="licensing requirements page" href="/drugs/licensing.aspx">licensing requirements page</a>.</p>

